<br>
ikitiar and eashan are not as hard as otehr mobs in tovn, but they do drop desired loot (at least 1 or 2 per).<br>
<br>
The whole point of rotations is you give, and you take:<br>
<br>
I give up 2 avatar of war kills, to ensure i will always get one (every 3rd spawn) if i want it.  I give up 2/3 of the xerkish spawns in sra, i give up 1/2 of the hp spawns, 1/2 of the blood spawns, 1/5th of the dozekar spawns, 1/x of etc etc etc...I trade smaller loot intake to my guild for order.  I sacrifice, but in exchange i know that if i want to, i can kill any mob in the game, regularly (depending on # of rotation member).  <br>
<br>
Most rotations are mob based, because they are clear cut cases of: kill this mob, loot it, grats... there are also instance of other situations. For instance:<br>
<br>
Plane of fear: it probably has 350 mobs in it. Do we put each mob on rotation?  HAH no!... we put the zone on rotation (and separately the god, because the zone pops every 12h, the god every 7d.  ToV is basically 3 zones, all connected.<br>
<br>
ToVwest (the 3 dragons), HoT, and ToVnorth.  It has been decided from the very first inception of rotation, that once you were admitted to the rotation, you had all 15 (ikky, eash, arry, felsh, dagarn, kriezen, mirelenna, koi, vyemm, zlex, cek, sev, nev, jor, vulak (until removed)) protected for 48hours.  Your 'passage' to this protection is by killing arrynar (because you basically can only kill 2/15 of tov until you kill him... after this, in all likelyhood you can steamroll the rest.  <br>
<br>
If people take it upon themselves to snipe the front 2, for loot or whatever reason, then they again are sitting on the fence:  if you can kill ikky/eash, in all likelyhood you can kill king t, statue, dain, zlandicar.  So, under this sccenario, you are using double standards with the rotation, that is: you enjoy the safety of having mobs protected for you, uncontested and then 'rebel' against the rotations when it doesnt suit your needs/wants.  <br>
<br>
If people begin to snipe ikky/each, then he will in effect go FFA, which will, in effect remove him from existence in the game (trust me).  So, this is where you 'give' - you exercise discipline, and avoid sniping ikky/eash (unless you have genuine intent to try arry, win or loose - if you are genuinely making an effort to enter the rotation, you are in the right here), and meet the prereqisites to enter the tovN rot, from there, you too will enjoy a GUARANTEED shot/kill/loot of ikky/eash/ and beyond every X weeks until this game goes out of business, or you move on.<br>
<br>
Is it that hard to understand?? <p><a href="http://www.drow.org/eq/roster/viewprofile.php?name=Emil">Emil Sinclair</a><br>
