Two, killing Eashen and Ikky isn't worth the clearing the hallway leading up the the hub, clearing the hub, clearing the rampage mobs, then killing 2 mobs which drop crap loot.<br>
Third, it would logically require a seperate Ikky and a seperate Eashen votation because some guilds could kill Ikky and not Eashen.<br>
Fourth, there would be very little interest in the rotation because it's a ton of work that usually results in useless loot.  The trouble with this is that Ikky/Eashen would be left up for days, getting passed multiple times, while other guilds are waiting on them to die in order to get into NToV.<br>
Fifth, it sets a precedent for splitting up the rest of NToV on all their own rotations.<br>
Sixth, it just doesn't make any goddamned sense.<br>
<br>
Consider this scenario:  BotS, Tindi, and NB are on the rotation, and in this example, the rotation is in that order. (not sure what it is in reality)  LoM (to pull a guild out of my ass) decides they want to start killing Ikky/Eashen.  For whatever reason, bots, tindi, and NB agree.  The ikky rotation is BotS, Tindi, and NB, and then LoM adds themselves in after BotS.  BotS clears NToV and kills ikky/Eashen.  Next turn comes up, it's Tindi's turn in NToV and LoM's turn on ikky/Eashen.  LoM isn't ready to kill ikky/Eashen for whatever reason, and kills him the next day, forcing Tindi to wait a day to start NToV.  The next day, LoM are breaking into NToV and Tindi comes in after them to kill NToV.  Training, swearing, and much unhappiness ensues. (ala HoT of now)  LoM kills ikky/Eashen, Tindi clears NToV.  Next week, it's NB's turn in NToV and Tindi's turn for Eashen/Ikky.  Tindi has better things to do than kill Eashen/Ikky, for instance, masturbating, doing tradeskills, and making fun of Alistriwen's signatures.  They pass on Ikky/Eashen.  NB kills NToV, including Ikky/Eashen, as normal.  Next week, it's BotS's turn for all of NToV again.  See what happened?  Tindi is excluded from killing Eashen/Ikky entirely, as well as causing a fukton of tension between LoM and Tindi.  Is that fair?<br>
<br>
A new scenario.  NToV rotation is as stated above, ikky/Eashen rotation is BotS, LoM, FK, VoLS, Tindi, NB.  Bots kills all of NToV.  LoM is up for Ikky/Eashen, Tindi for NToV.  It's noon on Monday.  Tindi forms for NToV.  LoM is nowhere to be found.  3pm, LoM starts forming for Ikky/Eashen.  They don't have enough members to do it.  It's now 5pm.  They pass.  FK is busy with whatever, they'll do it tomorrow.  It's noon on Tuesday.  Tindi forms for NToV.  FK doesn't have a force on yet.  4pm, they the people on.  The form, start clearing.  5pm.  Clear up to the hub, pull the first couple rampage wyverns, it's 6pm.  They wipe to rampage wyverns.  They coffin, re-clear to wyverns, kill Ikky/Eashen, it's 10pm.  They get 2 pieces of crappy loot.  Tindi reclears picture hall, hub, rampage wyverns, kills Roy, it's now 1am and they go to bed.  Tindi reforms at noon on Wednesday, starts clearing the rest of NToV on their second day, having cleared nothing other than... Roy, which is right about where they should have been 2 days earlier at 3-4 in the afternoon.  They clear, but since they got so little done the day before, and for whatever reason the going is slow today, and they have to pass the twins because it's too late for them to keep going, and their 48 hourse have expired.  Monday and Tuesday were mostly a waste for them.  This is ludicriously unfair. (This already happens occasionally with Statue/AOW.  NB will be up for AoW, but have to wait on &lt;insert random guild here&gt; to kill statue in order to get Idol to pop to trigger AoW, and will be delayed an extra day or two.  This isn't much of a problem because setting up for AoW takes about as long as it takes to buff.  It would be a huge problem in ToV because of how many mobs you have to clear, deaths in SG and WW, the inacessability of the zone, etc.)<br>
<br>
Because of all this, BotS, Tindi, and NB will all say no to an ikky/Eashen rotation.  Since rotations are pretty much a consensus by the guilds who kill them, (right now, BotS, Tindi, and NB are the only people who kill them) a seperate Ikky/Eashen rotation won't happen.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You aren't trying at all to be fair to other lil guilds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
/boggle<br>
<br>
I'm sure the larger guilds wouldn't mind going FFA for a week or two.  You know, demo what &quot;not being fair to other lil guilds&quot; really means.  You wanted to kill Talendor/Sev/Trak/Gore?  Sorry, we mana burned them.  Most of it went to alts, and what didn't went to the bazaar.  A wizard looted and destroyed the pally books cuz none of our pallies needs it, and giving you epics makes it easier for you to steal our mobs.  You wanted to kill Vindi?  We killed him with 9 people at 4am last night.  Oh yeah, a level 60 shammy just solo'd Lodi.  Some of our alts want stuff from Va`Dyn so we're gonna kill him with the 2 xp groups we already have there.  You wanted statue?  We just did him with 3 groups.  We dropped KT with our morning crew.  The Euro guilds killed rhag 1 and 2.  HoT farming?  Well, we need to kill doze.  I hope you don't mind while we overrun your camp.<br>
<br>
&quot;not being fair to other lil guilds&quot; = &quot;lil guilds never kill anything&quot;.  By anything, I mean ANYTHING.  NB, tindi, and bots can all mobilize 4 times faster than you can.  In order to kill any given mob, you need to beat <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> all three of them</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  You can't win, and you won't.  Your members will realize this, decide &quot;if you can't beat 'em, join 'em&quot; and the larger guilds will skim off your best equipped members.  This is what happens on every server other than the Rathe.  The largest of the smaller guilds can do little better than fear and first floor hate raids, maybe hitting up PoG every now and then.  The largest one or two guilds monopolize everything else.<br>
<br>
If it was NB/bots/Tindi's desire to kill everything they wanted to kill whenever they wanted to do it, they would do so.  Period.  We don't do this because screwing people over doesn't make us giddy.  We try our hardest to make all rotations the fairest they can be, and if they aren't as fair as they can be, we change them.  We want a fair rotation system just as much as you do. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
